Budget Tracker
A simple Python script I put together to keep track of daily income and expenses from the command line. It saves all your transactions to a local SQLite database so you don't lose your data when you close the app.

What it does
Logs transactions: Add your income or expenses along with a custom amount and a short description.

Auto-timestamps: You don't have to enter the date; the script grabs the exact time you add the entry.

Stores data locally: uses SQLite3 to store data in a budget_tracker database.db file on your computer.

No dependencies: It only uses Python's built-in libraries (sqlite3 and datetime), so you don't need to run pip install for anything.

How to use it
Make sure you have Python 3 installed.

Download or clone budget_tracker.py to your computer.

Open your terminal, navigate to the folder where you saved the file, and run:

Bash
python budget_tracker.py
The first time you run it, it will automatically create the database file for you. From there, just follow the on-screen menu:

Plaintext
Budget Tracker Menu:
1. Add Transaction
2. View Transactions
3. Exit
Database structure
If you want to poke around the database yourself, the transactions table is set up like this:

id (Primary Key)

date (Text)

type (Text - usually 'income' or 'expense')

amount (Real number)

description (Text)

